titleAfrika Islam (born Charles Glenn, 1967, New York City) also known as the "Son of Bambaataa", is an American hip-hop producer.{{cite web}}
LifeHe started his career in 1977 joining Rock Steady Crew. He was 10 years old back then. In the 1980s he moved to Los Angeles where he co-produced Ice T's early albums Rhyme Pays and Power.
In the late 1990s, Afrika Islam joined German techno icon Westbam to form Mr. X and Mr. Y, a techno duo that made commercial techno with Electro influences.He also recorded with Kalwi & Remi. A duo from Poland.
